# Affiliate Module Rules

References:

- docs/product-requirements.md
- docs/database-design.md
- docs/enums.md
- docs/user-flows.md
- docs/api-specification.md

---

# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- Affiliate Link Generation
- Deeplink Generation
- Click Tracking
- Affiliate Link History
- Campaign Mapping
- Cashback Estimation

This module is the revenue engine of the platform.

---

# MVP Affiliate Provider

Primary Provider:

Accesstrade

Future Providers:

- Ecomobi
- MasOffer
- In-house affiliate sources

For MVP:

Only Accesstrade is supported.

Do not build multi-provider complexity yet.

---

# Supported Affiliate Sources

MVP Supported:

- Shopee
- Lazada (future-ready)

Initially optimize for Shopee.

---

# Core Flow

User

↓

Paste Product URL

↓

Validate URL

↓

Generate Tracking Parameters

↓

Call Accesstrade Deeplink API

↓

Save AffiliateLink

↓

Return Short Link

---

# AffiliateLink Entity

Represents a generated affiliate link.

Suggested fields:

- Id
- UserId
- OriginalUrl
- AffiliateUrl
- ShortUrl
- CampaignId
- Sub1
- Sub2
- Sub3
- Provider
- CreatedAt
- UpdatedAt

---

# Source Of Truth

AffiliateLink table is the source of truth.

Never reconstruct links from order data.

Always persist generated links.

---

# Supported URL Rules

Allowed:

✓ Shopee Product URLs

✓ Shopee Campaign URLs

✓ Shopee Mall URLs

Future:

- Lazada URLs

---

Reject:

- Empty URLs
- Invalid URLs
- Unsupported domains

---

# URL Validation Rules

Must validate:

- Valid URL format
- Supported domain
- Non-empty

Validation belongs in:

GenerateAffiliateLinkValidator

Not in controller.

---

# Campaign Rules

Campaign configuration must be externalized.

Do NOT hardcode:

```csharp
campaignId = "4348614231480407268";
```

Use configuration.

Example:

AffiliateOptions

↓

ShopeeCampaignId

---

# Tracking Rules

Every generated link must contain tracking identifiers.

Required:

Sub1

Optional:

Sub2

Sub3

---

# Sub Parameter Strategy

Sub1 = UserId

Example:

```text
sub1 = user_123
```

Purpose:

Associate future commissions to user.

---

Sub2

Reserved for:

Traffic Source

Example:

```text
web
mobile
```

---

Sub3

Reserved for:

Marketing Campaign

Future usage.

---

# Deeplink Generation Rules

All deeplink generation must use:

IAccesstradeClient

Never call HttpClient directly.

---

Infrastructure Layer Responsibility

AccesstradeClient

↓

Generate Deeplink

↓

Return Affiliate URL

---

# Generate Affiliate Link Command

Example:

GenerateAffiliateLinkCommand

Input:

- OriginalUrl

Output:

- AffiliateUrl
- ShortUrl

---

# Duplicate Generation Rules

Users may generate the same URL multiple times.

This is allowed.

Do not block duplicates.

Each request generates a new tracking record.

---

# Click Tracking Rules

Every generated link should create a click tracking record.

Suggested Entity:

AffiliateClick

Fields:

- Id
- UserId
- AffiliateLinkId
- ClickedAt
- Source

---

Purpose:

Analytics

Future fraud detection

Conversion tracking

---

# Cashback Rules

Affiliate Module may estimate cashback.

Actual cashback comes from Orders Module.

Important:

Estimated Cashback

≠

Confirmed Cashback

Never treat estimated cashback as balance.

---

# Cashback Rate Rules

Cashback percentage should come from configuration.

Example:

Shopee

80%

Meaning:

Platform receives:

100%

User receives:

80%

Platform keeps:

20%

---

Never hardcode percentages.

---

# Provider Abstraction

Use abstraction.

Example:

IAffiliateProvider

Methods:

GenerateLinkAsync()

Future providers can implement same contract.

---

MVP implementation:

AccesstradeAffiliateProvider

---

# Error Handling

Common failures:

- Invalid URL
- Accesstrade unavailable
- Invalid campaign
- API timeout

Return business-friendly messages.

Do not expose provider internals.

---

# Rate Limiting

Protect affiliate generation endpoint.

Examples:

100 requests/hour/user

Configurable.

---

# Analytics Rules

Track:

- Total Links Generated
- Total Clicks
- Top Users
- Conversion Rate

Analytics should never affect transaction processing.

---

# Dashboard Integration

Affiliate Module contributes:

Dashboard Metrics

Examples:

- Links Generated
- Clicks
- Estimated Cashback

---

# Security Rules

Never trust:

- UserId from frontend
- Provider response blindly

Always validate current authenticated user.

---

# Logging Rules

Log:

✓ Link Generation

✓ Provider Errors

✓ API Failures

✓ Campaign Failures

---

Never log:

✗ Tokens

✗ Secrets

✗ Authorization headers

---

# Frontend Rules

Affiliate Link Page

Responsibilities:

- Paste URL
- Submit request
- Display generated link
- Copy link

---

Frontend must not:

- Build affiliate links manually
- Generate sub parameters
- Calculate cashback

Backend owns all logic.

---

# Required Endpoints

POST

/api/v1/affiliate-links/generate

Purpose:

Generate affiliate link.

---

GET

/api/v1/affiliate-links

Purpose:

User history.

---

GET

/api/v1/affiliate-links/{id}

Purpose:

Link details.

---

# Required Commands

GenerateAffiliateLinkCommand

---

# Required Queries

GetAffiliateLinksQuery

GetAffiliateLinkDetailQuery

---

# Testing Requirements

Must Test

URL Validation

✓ Valid URL

✓ Invalid URL

✓ Unsupported Domain

---

Link Generation

✓ Success

✓ Provider Failure

✓ Timeout

---

Tracking

✓ Sub1 generated

✓ User association correct

---

Security

✓ User cannot access another user's links

